@startuml recall-consolidate-query-union
' Query union sequence: resolve the latest shard + its consolidated_lsn
' watermark -> search Recall (lsn > watermark, brute-force exact) and the
' Consolidate shard (FAISS via the SSD/RAM cache) -> merge: square pgvector
' L2 -> L2^2 (metric alignment), recall-wins dedup, suppress recall-tombstoned
' ids, sort ascending, take top_k. Also shows the no-shard recall/ephemeral
' branch and the mode label (which always reflects the cold cache only).

title Query union: search Recall + Consolidate, then merge (RB_RECALL on)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "client" as client
participant "query_dp\n(run_query)" as dp
database "shard_catalog\n(consolidated_lsn)" as catalog
participant "_hot_search\n(FAISS via SSD/RAM cache)" as cold
database "Recall\n(pgvector, recall_search)" as recall

client -> dp : POST /query {vector, top_k, filter}
activate dp

== Resolve the seam (I3: pair the watermark to the shard actually read) ==

dp -> catalog : list_shards -> latest shard S
alt shard S exists
  dp -> cold : search S (FAISS, L2^2)\nvia SSD/RAM cache
  activate cold
  cold --> dp : cold hits (L2^2) +\nOUT: the exact shard row resolved,\nits consolidated_lsn = W   [I3]
  deactivate cold
else no shard yet (list_shards empty)
  note right of dp #E9F7E9
    Watermark W = 0 -> every Recall row qualifies.
    Answer SYNCHRONOUSLY from Recall (read-your-writes
    for a brand-new dataset). Does NOT fall to ephemeral.
  end note
end

== Search Recall with the RESOLVED watermark (brute-force exact) ==

dp -> recall : recall_search WHERE tenant, dataset,\nlsn > W (the resolved shard's wm, NOT a fresh list_shards),\nfilter  [I3]
activate recall
note right of recall
  Brute-force exact L2 over the SMALL recall partition.
  Score computed as power(embedding <-> q, 2) = L2^2,
  so it merges DIRECTLY with the cold shard's FAISS L2^2.
  Returns BOTH live matches and the FULL set of recall ids
  above W (incl. tombstoned / filtered-out / past-top_k).
end note
recall --> dp : recall hits (L2^2) + full recall-id set above W
deactivate recall

== Merge ==

dp -> dp : (1) METRIC ALIGNMENT -- square pgvector L2 -> L2^2\n(over identical un-normalised vectors; the most likely silent bug)
dp -> dp : (2) DEDUP recall-wins -- any cold hit whose id is in the\nfull recall-id-set-above-W is dropped (Recall is newer)
dp -> dp : (3) SUPPRESS tombstones -- a deleted/filtered recall row\nsuppresses its cold twin but contributes NO match\n(only a filter-passing LIVE recall row adds a match)
dp -> dp : (4) SORT ascending by L2^2, take top_k

== mode label (reflects the COLD cache only, never Recall) ==

note over dp #FDF3E7
  cold resolved (warm) -> mode=hot   | cold resolved (load) -> mode=cold
  no cold shard, recall answered -> mode=recall
  no cold shard, no recall row    -> mode=ephemeral (+ job_id)
  So hot/cold does NOT imply Recall was idle -- the label
  only describes the cold cache state.
end note

dp --> client : {matches, mode, ...}
deactivate dp

@enduml
